For letters and words there are seperate diretories.

The directories are structured like this:
compareResults.sh - Tells you the percentage correct
generateGtModels.sh - Generates the language model files with Good Turing
gtModelLangId.pl - the perl part of generateGtModels
letterLangId.pl - the letter bigram perl script that runs the test
generateModels.sh - Generates the language model files with Add One
modelLangId.pl - the Add one version of the model generator
generateResults.sh - the perl Results generator
rm_files.sh - cleans out the generated files

Add One Letter:
$ ./generateModels.sh
$ ./generateResults.sh
$ ./compareResults.sh
98% accuracy

Good Turing Letter:
$ ./generateGtModels.sh
$ ./generateResults.sh
$ ./compareResults.sh
99% accuracy

Add One Word:
$ ./generateModels.sh
$ ./generateResults.sh
$ ./compareResults.sh
99% accuracy

Good Turing Word:
$ ./generateGtModels.sh
$ ./generateResults.sh
$ ./compareResults.sh
99% accuracy
